**Key insight on variance drag:**

> "The simple average return is approximately equal to the compound return plus one-half of the variance. For example, Domestic Stocks has a simple average return of 14 percent, a modeled standard deviation of 12 percent, and a standard deviation of 20 percent. The simple average return of 14 percent is approximately equal to the compound annual return of 12 percent plus one-half of the variance (standard deviation squared)."

- Calculation: 14 percent ≈ 14 - 12 + .5(.20)² ≈ 14 = 14 percent

> "This simple equation (that is, compound annual return should be used as the expected return input to a portfolio optimization program."

